## Description {#details}

A node of a memory dependency graph.

A <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mca/lsunit/memorygroup">MemoryGroup</a> describes a set of instructions with same memory dependencies.

By construction, instructions of a <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mca/lsunit/memorygroup">MemoryGroup</a> don&#39;t depend on each other. At dispatch stage, instructions are mapped by the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mca/lsunit">LSUnit</a> to MemoryGroups. A <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/sys/memory">Memory</a> group identifier is then stored as a &quot;token&quot; in field Instruction::LSUTokenID of each dispatched instructions. That token is used internally by the <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/mca/lsunit">LSUnit</a> to track memory dependencies.
